            "text": "deficiency [4, 5] . Another reason for this absence could be that G6PD deficiency in the countries most affected by COVID-19 is rare and/or of the mild type. In Hubei province in China, the origin of COVID-19, the incidence of G6PD deficiency is only 0.098% and about 50% of these are due to WHO class III mild type [6] . We are anticipating that a report outlining the association between G6PD deficiency and COVID-19 may come from countries in which severe G6PD deficiency is very common. Such report is needed urgently. In Saudi Arabia, G6PD deficiency is not included in the list of diseases requiring additional precautionary measures to reduce risk of COVID-19. As per the traditional notion, \"absence of evidence is not evidence of absence\", it may be prudent to include G6PD deficiency in this list.",
            "cite_spans": [
